5 A BILL
6 TO BE ENTITLED
7 AN ACT
8
9 Relating to license tags and plates; to amend Section
10 32-6-130, Code of Alabama 1975, to authorize surviving spouses
11 of deceased "Disabled Veteran" license plate recipients to be
12 issued "Disabled Veteran Spouse" license plates; and to make
13 nonsubstantive, technical revisions to update the existing
14 code language to current style.
15 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA:
16 Section 1. Section 32-6-130, Code of Alabama 1975, is
17 amended to read as follows:
18 "§32-6-130
19 (a) Any veteran, as defined in Section 31-5-1, who is a
20 resident of this state and who is suffering a physical
21 disability which that requires that any motor vehicle he or
22 she operates be equipped with special mechanical control
23 devices or whose physical disability exceeds 50 percent, upon
24 application accompanied by proof of eligibility to the judge
25 of probate of the county for the special license plates
26 provided herein, as may be prescribed by the State Department
27 of Revenue, and upon payment of five dollars ($5), unless
28 exempted from the payment of such the fee by law, shall be
Page 1

exempted from the payment of such the fee by law, shall be
HB102 Engrossed
29 issued license plates, by the judge of probate as provided by
30 law, for private or pleasure motor vehicles, upon which, in.
31 In lieu of the number now prescribed by law shall be inscribed
32 in legible letters the words, "Disabled Veteran," and shall
33 designate the branch of service and an identifying number as
34 prescribed by the State Department of Revenue shall be
35 designated. The plates shall not be transferable. The fee
36 established by this section shall be in lieu of the regular
37 license fee now required for motor vehicles and shall be used
38 to defray the cost of issuing the distinctive license plates.
39 (b) In lieu of applying the registration fee of five
40 dollars ($5) to the disabled veteran license plate category
41 provided for in subsection (a), the registration fee may be
42 applied to any license plate category in which the disabled
43 veteran qualifies to obtain a license plate. Any additional
44 fee required for a plate from a distinctive or personalized
45 license plate category shall still be required in order to
46 obtain the plate.
47 (c)(1) There is established a "Disabled Veteran Spouse"
48 license plate to be issued to a surviving spouse of a
49 "Disabled Veteran" license plate recipient pursuant to this
50 subsection.
51 (2) The surviving spouse of a deceased "Disabled
52 Veteran" license plate recipient shall be issued a new
53 "Disabled Veteran Spouse" license plate for one private motor
54 vehicle owned by the surviving spouse for the remainder of the
55 spouse's lifetime or until the spouse's remarriage, upon:
56 a. Returning the "Disabled Veteran" license plate to
Page 2

a. Returning the "Disabled Veteran" license plate to
HB102 Engrossed
57 the judge of probate or other issuing official;
58 b. Providing proof of marriage to the disabled veteran;
59 and
60 c. Paying an issuance fee of five dollars ($5) in lieu
61 of all other regular fees for license plates.
62 (3) This subsection shall not be construed to permit a
63 "Disabled Veteran Spouse" license plate recipient to park in
64 any parking zone designated reserved for handicapped
65 individuals with disabilities."
66 Section 2. This act shall become effective on October
67 1, 2027.
